(548, 1, '2011-12-12 09:32:52', '2011-12-12 09:32:52', '<strong><span><span>International Initiative private </span></span><strong><span><span>,</span></span></strong><span><span> Jokkolabs is an "action tank" </span></span><span><span>that identifies and supports innovative ideas from entrepreneurs in the digital economy, cultural industries and media to accelerate the competitiveness of nations and prosperity for all. It is not for profit and launched in <strong>Dakar (Senegal) ,</strong></span></span></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong><span><span>"Jokko"</span></span></strong><span><span> is a term Wolof, Senegal''s majority language, born of the combination of </span></span><strong><span><span>"Joxko"</span></span></strong><span><span> meaning</span></span><strong><span><span>"give him"</span></span></strong><span><span> and </span></span><strong><span><span>"Jotko"</span></span></strong><span><span> meaning </span></span><strong><span><span>"the join"</span></span></strong><span><span> . </span><span>It is used to express the concepts of communication, exchange, sharing and integration into a community. </span><span>Thus, Jokkolabs carries values ​​that go beyond an area of creativity and innovation. </span><span>It is above all a </span></span><a href="http://jokkolabs.net/community.html"><span><span>human adventure</span></span></a><span><span> .</span></span>\r\n\r\n<strong>Jokkolabs</strong> is a laboratory of ideas, action-oriented. It is run by a dynamic learning community of entrepreneurs - catalysts and change agents - who are engaged on the challenges of tomorrow to create positive change and invent a better world. This movie revolves around a virtual space and coworking space - center of technological innovation and social - called JokkoSpace.\r\n\r\nWith  <strong>Jokkolabs</strong> Senegal, the first phase of this initiative, we intend to encourage and support reflection and experimentation with technological and social innovation in particular in Africa, a continent deeply touched by the crisis, but full of wealth and opportunity. Based in Dakar (Senegal), Senegal Jokkolabs officially opened on 10/10/10 a Technology Innovation Centre and Social <strong>JokkoSpace</strong> ,  <strong><em>first coworking space in West Africa!</em></strong>\r\n\r\nEnd of the world of hackers and free culture, our approach to innovation is inclusive. It aims to reflect and experiment with new ways to meet unmet social needs. To face the challenges of economic, social, environmental and cultural of this century, it is important to bring all stakeholders of the company to invent new solutions together.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Jokkolabs', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '533-revision-6', '', '', '2011-12-12 09:32:52', '2011-12-12 09:32:52', '', 533, 'http://cowobo.org/uncategorized/533-revision-6/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(46, 1, '2011-10-04 11:31:44', '2011-10-04 11:31:44', 'Coders Without Borders is a global platform aimed at the development of websites and software with clear social and/or ecological aims.\n\nWhile there already is a plethora of software available with social or ecological aims, or with the aim to aid the work of social and ecological organizations, there is as of yet no platform that maps, showcases and combines these projects and facilitates the development of new ones.\n\nWe hope to fill this hiatus by setting up:\n<ul>\n	<li>A database of existing projects and ideas</li>\n	<li>An information portal or showcase, to increase awareness of the potential and actual benefits of IT in the work of social/ecological organizations</li>\n	<li>A communication platform, to facilitate exchange:</li>\n<ul>\n	<li>between coders sharing expertise,</li>\n	<li>between coders and social/ecological organizations, sharing ideas and building knowledge,</li>\n	<li>between coders, organizations and potential donors, creating an environment for the development of tools, software and websites for social and/or ecological purposes</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\nIn summary, we aim to be\n<ul>\n	<li><em>a source of inspiration</em> for coders,</li>\n	<li><em>a showcase</em> of the potential social and ecological benefits of IT,</li>\n	<li><em>a source of expertise</em> on the principles of social / ecological coding</li>\n	<li><em>a thinktank</em> aimed at finding new ways in which IT can help</li>\n	<li><em>a facilitator</em> of the actual development of software and websites with a clear social and/or ecological aim</li>\n</ul>\nFor more information on how we hope to achieve our aims, please refer to our more extensive plans.', 'What is Coders Without Borders?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'what-is-coders-without-borders', '', '', '2011-10-29 08:15:42', '2011-10-29 08:15:42', '', 0, 'http://coders-borders.net/?p=46', 0, 'post', '', 0),
