(461, 1, '2011-10-03 13:01:03', '2011-10-03 13:01:03', 'CBONGO sites is a website builder for NGOs (Non-Governmental Organizations) and other non-profit organizations. It is built using solely open source software and released under a wholly free license (<a href="http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html" target="_new">GNU/GPL</a>). It is based on <a href="http://wordpress.org/" target="_new">WordPress</a> and a number of WordPress plugins (see our<a title="Developers" href="http://cbongosites.org/developers/#credits">developer</a> page). Its features include:\n<ul>\n	<li><strong>Easy to use maintenance interface</strong> – users can edit their websites with little or no computer skills. All editing happens on the webpage yourself and What-You-See-Is-What-You-Get (WYSIWYG). Users never have to deal with any back-end interfaces for building or maintaining their websites.</li>\n	<li><strong>Draft pages in Microsoft®</strong> <strong>Word </strong>- cbongo sites includes an easy-to-use uploader for Word and Excel pages including images, which allows users to first make and lay-out their pages in a familiar desktop environment before adding them to their websites.</li>\n	<li><strong>Mobile website</strong> – as the mobile phone has become one of the main internet interfaces in Africa, cbongo sites automatically generates a mobile accessible website, without any effort from the user.</li>\n	<li><strong>Automatic installation</strong> – there are multiple ways to install cbongo sites, all requiring little computer skills. Users only have to enter the information their web host has supplied them with and their site will install itself. The installer checks which installation is most appropriate for the server configuration and installs automatically. If an installation module still fails, users are automatically guided to the next alternative option.</li>\n	<li><strong>A collection of customizable lay-outs – </strong>when users start the tool for the first time, the are presented with the choice between a collection of standard lay-outs. For developers, there is an API that allows them to easily convert WordPress themes for full use with the cbongo sites framework.</li>\n	<li><strong>Set-up wizard </strong>- the user is guided through the designing of their website by a wizard interface. This set-up wizard guides the user through adding their site’s logo and header images and helps them select the colours for their site based on the colours of the used images.</li>\n	<li><strong>Content generator </strong>- after users have set the look-and-feel of the website, they can choose to start building the rest of their website using the WYSIWYG editors or first run our content generator, which generates basic versions of the most common pages for NGOs and CBOs.</li>\n	<li><strong>PayPal donation implementation</strong> – it is very easy to add a PayPal ‘Donate’ button to a cbongo website. Users just have to fill out the required fields, and a ‘Donate’ button will automatically be added to their website.</li>\n	<li><strong>Automatic updating </strong>- whenever there is an update to the cbongo sites core available, users will be prompted to have this update automatically downloaded and installed.</li>\n	<li><strong>Support updating </strong>- on top of the standard updates, cbongo sites includes the possibility of custom updates for specific websites. So, whenever a specific organization runs into a bug or requests a feature to be implemented, our support team has the possibility of making specific updates and scripts available, that can be downloaded and installed through the cbongo sites interface.</li>\n	<li><strong>Full WordPress flexibility </strong>- though cbongo sites is a heavy modification of the WordPress framework, it is essentially non-destructive. Advanced users and developers using cbongo sites (or who just want to implement the user interface) can still utilize <em>all </em>of the options and extensions the WordPress framework has to offer.</li>\n</ul>', 'CBONGO', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '87-revision', '', '', '2011-10-03 13:01:03', '2011-10-03 13:01:03', '', 87, 'http://cowobo.org/uncategorized/87-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(462, 1, '2011-10-05 11:31:46', '2011-10-05 11:31:46', '<span style="font-size: small">Infoweby focuses on affordable and socially responsible, informational website development. We are based in Zimbabwe. </span>\n<div>Having a website is essential in today''s world and we believe it should not cost a fortune. That''s why we only charge a one-time development fee and <span style="text-decoration: underline">nothing per month thereafter</span>.\n<div dir="ltr">\n<div>As a social business, our main goal is to <strong>alleviate poverty in Africa</strong> by:</div>\n<div>\n<ol>\n	<li><span style="font-size: x-small">Providing training and employment opportunities (the unemployment rate in Zimbabwe is over 80%)</span></li>\n	<li>Promoting gender equality (we pledge to hire at least 50% females)</li>\n	<li>Donating to charity (we donate 10% of our income to <a href="http://www.childfutureafrica.org/" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Child Future Africa</a> - an orphanage about 100 miles north of Harare)</li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Infoweby', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '125-revision', '', '', '2011-10-05 11:31:46', '2011-10-05 11:31:46', '', 125, 'http://cowobo.org/uncategorized/125-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
