(482, 1, '2011-10-04 11:31:44', '2011-10-04 11:31:44', 'Coders Without Borders is a global platform aimed at the development of websites and software with clear social and/or ecological aims.\n\nWhile there already is a plethora of software available with social or ecological aims, or with the aim to aid the work of social and ecological organizations, there is as of yet no platform that maps, showcases and combines these projects and facilitates the development of new ones.\n\nWe hope to fill this hiatus by setting up:\n<ul>\n	<li>A database of existing projects and ideas</li>\n	<li>An information portal or showcase, to increase awareness of the potential and actual benefits of IT in the work of social/ecological organizations</li>\n	<li>A communication platform, to facilitate exchange:</li>\n<ul>\n	<li>between coders sharing expertise,</li>\n	<li>between coders and social/ecological organizations, sharing ideas and building knowledge,</li>\n	<li>between coders, organizations and potential donors, creating an environment for the development of tools, software and websites for social and/or ecological purposes</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\nIn summary, we aim to be\n<ul>\n	<li><em>a source of inspiration</em> for coders,</li>\n	<li><em>a showcase</em> of the potential social and ecological benefits of IT,</li>\n	<li><em>a source of expertise</em> on the principles of social / ecological coding</li>\n	<li><em>a thinktank</em> aimed at finding new ways in which IT can help</li>\n	<li><em>a facilitator</em> of the actual development of software and websites with a clear social and/or ecological aim</li>\n</ul>\nFor more information on how we hope to achieve our aims, please refer to our more extensive plans.', 'What is Coders Without Borders?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '46-revision', '', '', '2011-10-04 11:31:44', '2011-10-04 11:31:44', '', 46, 'http://cowobo.org/uncategorized/46-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
