(497, 1, '2011-10-21 08:57:53', '2011-10-21 08:57:53', 'Coders Without Borders is a global platform aimed at the development of websites and software with clear social and/or ecological aims.\n\nWhile there already is a plethora of software available with social or ecological aims, or with the aim to aid the work of social and ecological organizations, there is as of yet no platform that maps, showcases and combines these projects and facilitates the development of new ones.\n\nWe hope to fill this hiatus by setting up:\n<ul>\n	<li>A database of existing projects and ideas</li>\n	<li>An information portal or showcase, to increase awareness of the potential and actual benefits of IT in the work of social/ecological organizations</li>\n	<li>A communication platform, to facilitate exchange:</li>\n<ul>\n	<li>between coders sharing expertise,</li>\n	<li>between coders and social/ecological organizations, sharing ideas and building knowledge,</li>\n	<li>between coders, organizations and potential donors, creating an environment for the development of tools, software and websites for social and/or ecological purposes</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\nIn summary, we aim to be\n<ul>\n	<li><em>a source of inspiration</em> for coders,</li>\n	<li><em>a showcase</em> of the potential social and ecological benefits of IT,</li>\n	<li><em>a source of expertise</em> on the principles of social / ecological coding</li>\n	<li><em>a thinktank</em> aimed at finding new ways in which IT can help</li>\n	<li><em>a facilitator</em> of the actual development of software and websites with a clear social and/or ecological aim</li>\n</ul>\nFor more information on how we hope to achieve our aims, please refer to our more extensive plans.', 'What is Coders Without Borders?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '46-revision-2', '', '', '2011-10-21 08:57:53', '2011-10-21 08:57:53', '', 46, 'http://cowobo.org/uncategorized/46-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(498, 1, '2011-10-21 08:57:11', '2011-10-21 08:57:11', 'Brazzaville sera au cœur de l’actualité des nouvelles technologies de l’information et de la communication en Afrique à travers un grand rendez-vous d’échange, d’apprentissage et de vulgarisation des nouveaux outils du domaine. Il s’agit d’Africa Web Summit qui se tiendra du 17 au 18 septembre 2011 au Centre culturel français (CCF). Parrainée par le ministère congolais des postes, des télécommunications et des nouvelles technologies de la communication, cette rencontre vise la participation à la réduction du fossé numérique entre le Nord et Sud, en offrant d’une part aux professionnels l’opportunité de partager les connaissances et expériences avec leurs homologues d’autres horizons et d’autre part, au public de s’imprégner de nouveaux outils.\n\nSi au départ, la prospérité économique reposait sur la production de l’acier et la construction des kilomètres de chemin de fer, maintenant elle se focalise ardemment sur la communication de l’information. Ainsi, en ce début du 21ème siècle, aucun pays ne peut vanter ses performances économiques, s’il ne dispose pas d’infrastructures modernes de communication. Les pays d’Asie et ceux dits émergents constituent la parfaite illustration, au regard de leur spectaculaire développement socioéconomique. L’Internet et ses applications, ainsi que d’autres supports de technologies de l’information sont devenus irréversibles dans la vie moderne.', 'Africa Web Summit 2011 - Congo', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '124-revision-4', '', '', '2011-10-21 08:57:11', '2011-10-21 08:57:11', '', 124, 'http://cowobo.org/uncategorized/124-revision-4/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(499, 1, '2011-10-19 14:54:18', '2011-10-19 14:54:18', '<span style="font-size: small">Infoweby focuses on affordable and socially responsible, informational website development. We are based in Zimbabwe. </span>\n<div>Having a website is essential in today''s world and we believe it should not cost a fortune. That''s why we only charge a one-time development fee and <span style="text-decoration: underline">nothing per month thereafter</span>.\n<div dir="ltr">\n<div>As a social business, our main goal is to <strong>alleviate poverty in Africa</strong> by:</div>\n<div>\n<ol>\n	<li><span style="font-size: x-small">Providing training and employment opportunities (the unemployment rate in Zimbabwe is over 80%)</span></li>\n	<li>Promoting gender equality (we pledge to hire at least 50% females)</li>\n	<li>Donating to charity (we donate 10% of our income to <a href="http://www.childfutureafrica.org/" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">Child Future Africa</a> - an orphanage about 100 miles north of Harare)</li>\n</ol>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>', 'Infoweby', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '125-revision-2', '', '', '2011-10-19 14:54:18', '2011-10-19 14:54:18', '', 125, 'http://cowobo.org/uncategorized/125-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
